SIMPLE: wishy-washy
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wishy-washy
<hw>Wish"y-wash`y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Wash</er>.]</ety> <def>Thin and pale; weak; without strength or
substance; -- originally said of liquids. Fig., weak-minded;
spiritless.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A weak <qex>wishy-washy</qex> man who had hardly any mind of his
own.</q> <rj><qau>A. Trollope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wishy-washy</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Wishy-washy
<hw>Wish"y-wash`y</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A weak or thin drink or
liquor; wish-wash.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wisket</ent>⟦br⟧
